content:
Although you choose input data when you create a recipe, if needed, you can add more data to an existing recipe. In CRM Analytics, Data Prep shows a separate Input node for each set of data that you add to the recipe.

Select the Add Data button and select the input data. You can select a CRM Analytics dataset, external connected objects, or Salesforce objects as the input data. Direct data refers to all Salesforce objects that aren't synced. To use direct data, bypass the sync step and access the data directly from the Salesforce object.

By default, the Custom Columns option is selected from the dropdown next to the list of column names. If you select multiple sets of input data, select each row one at a time to choose its columns. Click Next.

Data Prep adds a separate Input node to the graph for each input data selection. You can show more than 100 columns in preview if needed.

Save the recipe. When you add an Input node, all columns after the first 100 are hidden from preview by default.

Use data preview sampling to see a more accurate picture of your data at each node in Preview. Select Filtered Rows or All Column Values to populate a sample when needed.

When using direct data for recipes, bypass the sync step and access the latest data directly from the Salesforce object with each recipe run.
title: Adding Data to a Recipe in CRM Analytics
